diff --git a/deps/wurl/STATUS.md b/deps/wurl/STATUS.md
new file mode 100644
index 0000000..1cdac32
--- /dev/null
+++ b/deps/wurl/STATUS.md
@@ -0,0 +1,80 @@
+# wurl — plain-C WHATWG URL for txiki.js (ada-ectomy Phase 2)
+
+Replaces `deps/ada` (977 KB C++20 `ada.cpp`, txiki's only C++ TU) with plain
+C11. Implements exactly the `ada_c.h` subset that `src/url.c` consumes
+(58 functions); `src/url.c` compiles unchanged.
+
+## Files
+
+- `ada_c.h` — public header (subset, signature-compatible with ada's).
+- `wurl_common.{h,c}` — byte buffers, the seven WHATWG percent-encode sets
+  (written as spec-literal predicates, reviewable at a glance), percent
+  decode, strict UTF-8.
+- `wurl_url.c` — basic-URL state machine (all spec states incl. file/
+  windows-drive quirks), host parser (domain + IDNA L1', IPv4 dec/oct/hex,
+  IPv6, opaque hosts), punycode (RFC 3492), serialization, origin, the
+  ada_url API incl. all setters with state-override semantics.
+- `wurl_params.c` — URLSearchParams: raw-byte pair list,
+  form-urlencoded parse/serialize, stable sort by UTF-16 code units
+  (WTF-8-aware), iterators. Reproduces golden findings F2 (single leading
+  `?` strip in parse/reset) and F3 (raw-byte round-trip of invalid
+  percent-encoded UTF-8).
+- `idna_allow.h` — GENERATED IDNA L1' allow-bitmap (BMP bitmap 8 KB +
+  astral ranges); regenerate with the pinned oracle tjs:
+  `build/tjs/tjs run deps/wurl/gen-idna-allow.mjs > deps/wurl/idna_allow.h`
+- `gen-idna-allow.mjs` — the generator; probes the golden-oracle binary
+  (vendored ada 3.4.2) so the bitmap can never admit a codepoint the golden
+  rejects. Admission conditions + multi-codepoint safety argument documented
+  in the script header.
+
+## Build selection
+
+Top-level `CMakeLists.txt`: `option(TJS_USE_ADA ... ON)`. Default ON keeps
+upstream behavior (links ada). `-DTJS_USE_ADA=OFF` links wurl instead:
+
+```
+cmake -S . -B build-wurl -DCMAKE_BUILD_TYPE=Release -DTJS_USE_ADA=OFF
+cmake --build build-wurl
+```
+
+## IDNA ladder position: L1'
+
+Non-ASCII host labels are punycoded as-is when every codepoint is in the
+allow-bitmap (UTS-46-identity, context-free, NFC-safe — see generator);
+anything else fails the parse LOUDLY (TypeError). No silent mis-parse is
+possible below full UTS-46.
+
+## L2 (full UTS-46) TODO seams
+
+- `wurl_idna_allowed()` / `domain_label_to_ascii()` in `wurl_url.c`:
+  replace bitmap check with IdnaMappingTable lookup (mapping + status),
+  NFC via quickjs-ng's bundled libunicode (`unicode_normalize`), bidi +
+  joining-type validation tables.
+- `gen-idna-allow.mjs`: successor generator reads Unicode data files
+  (IdnaMappingTable.txt) instead of probing the oracle binary.
+
+## Verification (2026-07-09, build-wurl/tjs vs golden sha 3debd9af...)
+
+Phase-2 grading (untagged exact; tagged may reject-where-golden-succeeds,
+never value-diverge) — 0 failures across all 1,317 golden cases:
+
+| section | exact | accepted tagged rejects | failures |
+| --- | --- | --- | --- |
+| parse | 883/891 | 8 (loud throws) | 0 |
+| setters | 276/278 | 2 (forgiving no-op, soft-hyphen host) | 0 |
+| toascii | 63/87 | 24 (loud reject / host-setter no-op) | 0 |
+| percentEncoding | 7/7 | 0 | 0 |
+| searchParams | 54/54 | 0 | 0 |
+
+Every untagged case matches the golden byte-for-byte (including the F1
+NUL-truncation and F2/F3 quirks). All 34 accepted rejects are IDNA L1'
+classes: UTS-46-mapped codepoints (fullwidth forms, ideographic full stop,
+math alphanumerics, uppercase sharp-s, Ӏ/Ↄ), ignorables (soft hyphen, ZW*,
+Mongolian vowel separator, CGJ), ContextJ joiners (Sinhala/Persian ZWJ/
+ZWNJ), NFC compositions (≠ ≮ ≯, combining marks). Each is a LOUD reject
+(TypeError) or a spec-forgiving setter no-op — never a silent mis-parse.
+
+Note: the committed clode test `test/url-characterization.test.cjs` golden
+gate is a strict byte-compare, so with `CLODE_TJS=<build-wurl>/tjs` it
+reports exactly these 34 tagged deltas and nothing else; it goes fully
+green at L2.
diff --git a/deps/wurl/ada_c.h b/deps/wurl/ada_c.h
